radiographic_examinations.findings: Biometry not in accordance with gestational age indicating severe intrauterine growth restriction (IUGR); fetal morphological study revealed several abnormalities including absent cavum septum pellucidum, abnormal bridge of tissue, open midline in prefrontal area, hypoplastic cerebellum, present nasal bone, slightly flattened frontal area with prefrontal edema, mild ocular proptosis, normal cardiac study, normal male genitalia, fixed wrist joint, and feet in hyperflexion.
